   <body>
      <prereq>
         <ul>
            <li>At least one saved filter exists. <ph product="Exclude_PG_Content">For information on saving a filter, refer to <xref href="SaveFltr.xml">Saving a Filter</xref>.</ph>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </prereq>
      <context>
         <p>In the list page of a form, you can set a filter as default. On opening the list page, the page displays only records that match the filter criteria.</p>
         <p>The following procedure describes the steps todefine a defaultfilter.The<uicontrol>PROJECTS</uicontrol>list page is used as an example.</p>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>In the module menu, click <uicontrol>Projects</uicontrol>.

</p>
            <p>The list of projects you are invited to is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the tool bar, click <image href="../../Icons/Filter-Toolbar.png" placement="inline">
                  <alt>Filter</alt>
               </image> .
</p>
            <p>The <uicontrol>FILTERS</uicontrol> dialog box is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the <uicontrol>Select Filter</uicontrol> section, select the appropriate filter.
	</p>
            <p>Available options are filters defined for the page. <ph product="Exclude_PG_Content">For information on defining a filter, refer to <xref href="SaveFltr.xml">Saving a Filter</xref>.</ph>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <image href="../../Icons/Filter-Star.png" placement="inline">
                  <alt>Default</alt>
               </image>  to set the selected filter as default. 

</p>
            <p>On loading the page, the default filter is automatically applied.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
   </body>
